Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - I develop a tractable growth model that allows me to study analytically transition dynamics and welfare in response to a deficit-financed cut of the tax rate on distributed dividends. I then carry out a quantitative assessment of the Job Growth and Taxpayer Relief Reconciliation Act (JGTRRA) of 2003. I find that the Act produces?lower?steady-state growth despite the fact that the economy?s saving and employment ratios?rise. Most importantly, it produces a welfare?loss?of 19.34% of annual consumption per capita?a substantial effect driven by the fact that the steady-state growth rate falls from 2% to 1.08%.
ER  - 

